FAQs
What is the duration of the medical program at Humanitas University?
The Medicine and Surgery program at Humanitas University is six years long.

Is the medical program at Humanitas University taught in English?
Yes, the Medicine and Surgery program is taught entirely in English.

What is the HUMAT?
The Humanitas University Admissions Test (HUMAT) is an entrance exam that assesses applicants' knowledge in science subjects and critical thinking skills.

Does Humanitas University offer on-campus accommodation?
Yes, Humanitas University offers on-campus housing options for students.

Are degrees from Humanitas University recognized globally?
Yes, degrees from Humanitas University are recognized worldwide, providing graduates with numerous career opportunities.
